@@TJvScrollBox
<TITLEIMG TJvScrollBox>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.GridsAndContent.ScrollBoxes
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Supports extended features such as hot tracking, and responds to navigational key combinations.
Description
  TJvScrollBox is a scroll box that supports extended features such as hot tracking, and responds to
  navigational key combinations. 
  
  You can use OnMouseEnter and OnMouseLeave to alter the controls look or behavoir, when the user 
  moves the mouse pointer over the control. Alternatively, you can use property HotTrack to highlight 
  the scroll box automatically when the mouse passes over it.

  Use OnHorizontalScroll and OnVerticalScroll to take action when the user scrolls the specified
  scroll bar.

  Property HintColor can be used to set a different color of the Help hint boxes for the scroll box.
  
  TJvScrollBox scrolls the box in response to the following navigational key combinations:
  <TABLE>
  Key                 Action
  ---                 ------
  UP ARROW            Scrolls one line up. 
  DOWN ARROW          Scrolls one line down. 
  LEFT ARROW          Scrolls left by one unit.
  RIGHT ARROW         Scrolls right by one unit.
  PAGE DOWN + Shift   Scrolls right by the width of the window.
  PAGE DOWN           Scrolls one page down.
  PAGE UP + Shift     Scrolls left by the width of the window.
  PAGE UP             Scrolls one page up.
  HOME + Shift        Scrolls to the upper left.
  HOME                Scrolls to the left.
  END + Shift         Scrolls to the lower right.
  END                 Scrolls to the right.
  </TABLE>  
