@@TJvScrollBox.KeyDown
Summary
  Provides special processing when the user presses a key.
Description
  KeyDown scrolls the box in response to the following navigational key combinations:
  
  <TABLE>
  Key                 Action
  ---                 ------
  UP ARROW            Scrolls one line up. 
  DOWN ARROW          Scrolls one line down. 
  LEFT ARROW          Scrolls left by one unit.
  RIGHT ARROW         Scrolls right by one unit.
  PAGE DOWN + Shift   Scrolls right by the width of the window.
  PAGE DOWN           Scrolls one page down.
  PAGE UP + Shift     Scrolls left by the width of the window.
  PAGE UP             Scrolls one page up.
  HOME + Shift        Scrolls to the upper left.
  HOME                Scrolls to the left.
  END + Shift         Scrolls to the lower right.
  END                 Scrolls to the right.
  </TABLE>
Parameters
  Key   - The key on the keyboard. For non-alphanumeric keys, you must use WinAPI virtual key codes to
           determine the key pressed. For more information, search for virtual key codes in the Win32
           Developer's Reference (WIN32.HLP). 
  Shift - Indicates whether the Shift, Alt, or Ctrl keys are combined with the keystroke.
